<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: How to hack a pal game to a ntsc game!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9501&amp;p=103181#p103181"><![CDATA[
I did hack a few games, and it innolved mainly 2 thins :<br />- I had to find the pitch table, and multiply all values by 15/16 (NTSC-&gt;PAL), for PAL-&gt;NTSC you'd have to multiply them by 16/15<br />- Find where the game have timed code for special video effects, and adjust the clock cycles for PAL (usually you'd do this with trial and error).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Mon Nov 19, 2012 4:49 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
